criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Every adult patient over 40 years old, presenting with constipation or alternating
             change in bowel habits, with a differential diagnosis of suspected colorectal cancer.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients presenting with anaemia;

          -  Patients presenting with diarrhoea only for more than 6 weeks;

          -  Patients presenting with rectal bleeding;

          -  Patients who have undergone a previous whole-colon examination in the past 6 months;

          -  Patients who have been referred for a whole-colon examination to follow up already
             diagnosed colorectal cancer;

          -  Patients lacking capacity to give consent or participate in the study;

          -  Patients already taking part in any clinical trial of an investigational medicinal
             product (CTIMP);

          -  Prisoners

          -  Patients who are not fluent in English.
